  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Restorative Justice Tribunal in El Salvador</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The annual Restorative Justice Tribunal run by the Central American University UCA seeks to contribute to the struggle against impunity by encouraging access to justice, and the recovery of historical memory in El Salvador. It started in 2009, as an element of the UCA Truth Festival which has been running since 1998. The Truth Festival is an academic, cultural and artistic week of events promoting truth, justice and peace, with the aim of contributing to the construction of a peaceful and democratic society. The Festival coincides with the anniversary of the 1980 murder of Saint Oscar Romero and the date it commemorates has been recognised by the United Nations as the &quot;International Day for the Right to the Truth Concerning Gross Human Rights Violations and for the Dignity of Victims&quot;: http://www.un.org/en/events/righttotruthday/</narrative>
  </description>
